    {
      "memberType": "type",
      "docId": null,
      "fields": {
        "summary": "Specifies color primaries as defined by CICP (Coding-Independent Code Points, ITU-T H.273).",
        "remarks": "<format type=\"text/markdown\"><![CDATA[\n## Remarks\n\n`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` enumerates the color primary values defined by the CICP\nspecification (ITU-T H.273 / ISO/IEC 23091-2). These values identify the chromaticity\ncoordinates of the red, green, and blue primaries used in a color space.\n\nUse these values with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(SkiaSharp.SKColorspacePrimariesCicp,SkiaSharp.SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp)>\nto create a color space from standard CICP parameters.\n\n## Examples\n\n```csharp\nvar colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(\n    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec709,\n    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Rec709);\n```\n]]></format>",
        "remarksRequired": true
      }
    },
